GEOEXPOSURE DATA.title: Geoexposure data_1.5.1 element schema
GEOEXPOSURE DATA.description: Geoexposure data_1.5.1 element schema generated by the CEDAR Template Editor 2.7.1

propertyDescriptions.measures: Enter list of specific variables collected by the resource system. If the variables are part of a set of variables, then enter the set name, e.g., clinical labs for clinical laboratory tests (especially if the specific labs vary from individual to individual), or VOC if for a list of volatile organic chemicals. Copy measure terms from measure_list worksheet.
propertyDescriptions.measures_other: If terms are not included in the measue_list worksheet, enter them here.
propertyDescriptions.measurement_method: Method used to capture the measures.
propertyDescriptions.time_extent_end: Last year of data collection, if ongoing but not frequently updated, include latest date available and update regularly.
propertyDescriptions.temporal_resolution: The finest available temporal resolution (i.e., highest frequency, finest scale) from CV (# - preferred data).
propertyDescriptions.spatial_resolution: The finest spatial resolution of the data. If there are multiple resources and determining the highest spatial resolution is impractical, use "Other".
propertyDescriptions.spatial_resolution_other: If "Other" is selected in previous field, enter the finest spatial resolution of the data. May be a specific distance measure (e.g., '5 km’, ‘2 degrees’, and ‘2 degrees by 5 degrees’). Convert 40° 11.25′ to 40 degrees, 11 arc min, 25 arc sec.
propertyDescriptions.spatial_coverage: Maximum spatial coverage of the data, if specific regions list in next field.
propertyDescriptions.spatial_bounding_box: Boundary coordinates for the geographical region (should be included in the model spatial metadata).
propertyDescriptions.geometry_type: Type of geometric data, the file extension will be different for different types (# - preferred data).
propertyDescriptions.geometry_source: Source or provider of the geometry data.
propertyDescriptions.model_methods: If data are modeled, describe modeling method(s) used to generate the data.
propertyDescriptions.exposure_media: Media to which the phenomena is related.
propertyDescriptions.geographic_feature: The type of geographic feature associated with the data.
propertyDescriptions.geographic_feature_other: If "Other" was selected in the previous field, enter the type of geographic feature associated with the data.
propertyDescriptions.data_formats: Select the format(s) of data in the collection (# - preferred data).
propertyDescriptions.measurement_method_other: If "Other" is selected in previous field, enter the method used to capture the measure.
propertyDescriptions.model_methods_other: If "Other" is selected in the previous field, enter the name of the modeling method used.
propertyDescriptions.time_available_comment: Description of the time extent details if multiple times exist in the resource or if there are discontinuities over time.
propertyDescriptions.spatial_coverage_other: If "Other" is selected in previous field, enter the specific region covered here; avoid using special symbols following same convention as in spatial_resolution_other (e.g., convert 40° to 40 degrees.). Do not convert latitude, longitude pairs if given as decimal.
propertyDescriptions.geometry_source_other: If "Other" was selected in the previous field, enter the geometry source here.
propertyDescriptions.temporal_resolution_other: If "Other" is selected in the previous field, enter the finest temporal resolution here.
